==English==
===Noun===
'''doozy''' (''more colloquial spelling of'' '''doozie''')
#something that is [[extraordinary]].  Often used in the context of [[troublesome]], [[difficult]] or [[problematic]], but can be used positively as well.
#:''Most of the test was easy, but the last question was a '''doozy'''.''
#;Oft-mentioned (though apparently incorrect) origin: slang borrowing of Duesenberg[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duesenberg], a car from the 1920's and '30's (see also "Doozy" [http://www.worldwidewords.org/qa/qa-doo2.htm])
#''Amer.'' earlier also '''dosy'''